                <fr:title text="Modulus of complex polynomial attains a minimum value">Modulus of complex polynomial attains a minimum value</fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>theorem</fr:taxon>
                <fr:meta name="source"><fr:link href="/lankham-2016-linear/" title="Linear algebra as an introduction to abstract mathematics" uri="http://localhost:8000/lankham-2016-linear/" display-uri="lankham-2016-linear" type="local">Linear algebra as an introduction to abstract mathematics</fr:link> Lemma 3.1.3</fr:meta>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter><html:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon \mathbb {C}\to \mathbb {C}]]></fr:tex> be a polynomial function. Then there exists a <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[z_{0}\in \mathbb {C}]]></fr:tex> where <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[|f|]]></fr:tex> attains its minimum value in <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {R}]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link href="/alex-nelson/" title="Alex Nelson" uri="http://localhost:8000/alex-nelson/" display-uri="alex-nelson" type="local">Alex Nelson</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:date><fr:year>2025</fr:year><fr:month>12</fr:month><fr:day>9</fr:day></fr:date><fr:taxon>proof</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><html:p><html:strong>Case 1:</html:strong> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> is a constant polynomial. Then <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[|f|]]></fr:tex> attains its minimum value at every point in <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {C}]]></fr:tex>, so pick <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[z_{0}=0]]></fr:tex> and we're done.</html:p>

<html:p><html:strong>Case 2:</html:strong> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> is not a constant polynomial. Then we can write it out as <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f(z)=a_{n}z^{n}+…+a_{1}z+a_{0}]]></fr:tex> where <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n=\deg (f)]]></fr:tex> is the degree of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex>, with <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a_{n}\neq 0]]></fr:tex>. Set
<fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[A=\max \{|a_{0}|,…,|a_{n}|\}]]></fr:tex>
Then we have <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A/|a_{n}|\geq 1]]></fr:tex>, so
<fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[|f(z)|\geq |a_{n}||z|^{n}\left (1-\frac {A}{|a_{n}|}\sum ^{\infty }_{k=1}\frac {1}{|z|^{k}}\right )=|a_{n}||z|^{n}\left (1-\frac {A}{|a_{n}|}\frac {1}{|z|-1}\right )]]></fr:tex>
For all <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[z\in \mathbb {C}]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[|z|\geq 2]]></fr:tex>, we can simplify this lower bound as
<fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[|f(z)|\geq |a_{n}||z|^{n}\left (1-\frac {2A}{|a_{n}||z|}\right )]]></fr:tex>
This implies there exists an <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[R>0]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[|f(z)|>|f(0)|]]></fr:tex> for all <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[z\in \mathbb {C}]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[|z|>R]]></fr:tex>. Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[D\subseteq \mathbb {R}^{2}]]></fr:tex> be the close disk of radius <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[R]]></fr:tex> centered at the origin, then define <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[g\colon  D\to \mathbb {R}]]></fr:tex> by
<fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[g(x,y)=|f(x+\mathrm {i} y)|.]]></fr:tex>
Since <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[g]]></fr:tex> is continuous, we apply <fr:link href="/complex-000H/" title="Extreme value theorem" uri="http://localhost:8000/complex-000H/" display-uri="complex-000H" type="local">Extreme value theorem</fr:link> to obtain a point <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[(x_{0},y_{0})\in  D]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[g]]></fr:tex> attains a minimum at <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[(x_{0},y_{0})]]></fr:tex>. By the choice of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[R]]></fr:tex> we have that for <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[z\in \mathbb {C}\setminus  D]]></fr:tex>, <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[|f(z)|>|g(0,0)|\geq |g(x_{0},y_{0})|]]></fr:tex>. Therefore <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[|f|]]></fr:tex> attains its minimum at <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[z=x_{0}+\mathrm {i} y_{0}]]></fr:tex>.</html:p><html:span class="qed">∎</html:span></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
</fr:mainmatter>
